# Answering Telephones and Directing Calls

## Answering the Phone

When answering the phone, I will:

* Greet the caller with a friendly and professional tone
* Identify myself and the medical practice
* Take a message or provide assistance as needed

## Directing Calls to Appropriate Staff

When directing calls to appropriate staff, I will:

* Ask the caller for the reason for their call and the staff member they are trying to reach
* Check the schedule and availability of the staff member
* Transfer the call to the appropriate staff member or take a message if they are unavailable
* Follow up with the caller to ensure their needs are met

</OUTPUT_TEXT>
